  "conclusion": "With rowchunk force-flag forwarding fixed, forcing only the full-attention-layer MoE suffix to per-row selected-c1 is not a hidden/token repair. Rowchunk2 remains the generated-token-green control with no linear-projection drift and no full-attention stage/bit failures. Rowchunk3 still has L5 layer4 QKV/Z drift, the L6 generated-token failure, and L8 layer7 attn_input_pre_qkv/query/attn_context/mlp_input failures. Full-attention grouped-compact MoE alone is therefore eliminated under trustworthy forwarded execution; the remaining failure is inherited from the rowchunk3 layer3 full-attention trajectory before/around the context-output producer rather than from the MoE suffix.",
